European Stocks Rebound From Four-Week Low as Commodities Climb; BHP Gains

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-05-18T07:02:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/european-stocks-rebound-from-four-week-low-as-commodities-climb-bhp-gains.html
European stocks climbed for the first
time in five days, rebounding from a four-week low, as base
metals and oil led gains in commodities. Asian shares and U.S.
index futures advanced.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index gained 0.6 percent to 278.94 at
8:02 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  